!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

virtue /ˈvɜːtjuː/

(virtues) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Virtue is thinking and doing what is right and avoiding what is wrong. 正直的品性 

例： Virtue is not confined to the Christian world. 正直的品性并不限于基督教世界。 

2. N-COUNT A virtue is a good quality or way of behaving. 美德 

例： His virtue is patience. 他的美德就是耐心。 

3. N-COUNT The virtue of something is an advantage or benefit that it has, especially in comparison with something else. 优势; 益处 

例： There was no virtue in returning to Calvi the way I had come. 按我来的路线返回卡尔维并不可取。 

4. PHRASE You use by virtue of to explain why something happens or is true. 因为 [正式] 

例： The article stuck in my mind by virtue of one detail. 该文章因一细节而印入我脑海。

</div>

